# SASS Installation Steps

## Linux Installation (Optional)
1. Install nvm (Node Version Manager):
   ```bash
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
   ```
2. Exit the terminal using the `exit` command
3. Reopen the terminal
4. Install Node.js version 20.16 using nvm:
   ```bash
   nvm install 20.16
   ```

## Installation Anywhere (Optional)
If you have Node.js installed, install SASS using npm:
```bash
npm install sass -v 3.7.4
```

## Verification
To verify the installation, you can run:
```bash
sass --version
```
This should display the installed version of SASS (3.7.4). 